  89 -def _dir_filter(self): 

  90      # Using introspection, mimic dir() by adding up all of the __dicts__ 
  91      # for the current class and all base classes (type(self).__mro__ returns 
  92      # all of the classes that make it up) 
  93      # Basically filters by: 
  94      # __x__ OK 
  95      # __x bad 
  96      # _classname bad 
  97      def check(s): 
  98          if s.startswith('__'): 
  99              if s.endswith('__'): 
 100                  return True 
 101              else: 
 102                  return False 
 103          else: 
 104              for typename in typenames: 
 105                  if typename in s: 
 106                      return False 
 107              return True 

 108       
 109      keys=sum([list(c.__dict__.keys()) for c in type(self).__mro__], []) 
 110      typenames=["_%s" % c.__name__ for c in type(self).__mro__] 
 111      ret=[s for s in list(set(keys)) if check(s)] 
 112      ret.sort() 
 113      return ret
